Mark C. Biderman  Director, Atlas Energy Group, LLCAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 3 Board Members in 3 different organizations across 9 different industries.See Board Relationships71$106,167
Background

		Mr. Mark C. Biderman served as an Executive Vice President and the Chief Financial Officer at National Financial Partners Corp., from November 1999 to September 2008 and served as its Principal Accounting Officer. He has more than 33 years of financial services industry experience. From May 1987 to October 1999, Mr. Biderman served as a Managing Director and the Head of the Financial Institutions Group in the Corporate Finance Department of CIBC World Markets Group and ... its predecessor, Oppenheimer & Co., Inc. He served as Equity Analyst of Oppenheimer & Co. Inc., Research Division. Prior to investment banking, he served as an Equity Research Analyst, covering the commercial banking industry. Mr. Biderman served on the ''Institutional Investor'' All American Research Team from 1973 to 1985. He served as a Vice Chairman of National Financial Partners Corp. since April 07, 2008 until December 2008. Mr. Biderman has been an Independent Director at Full Circle Capital Corporation since August 2010. He has been an Independent Director of Apollo Commercial Real Estate Finance, Inc. since November 10, 2010.  Mr. Biderman has been a Director of Arkhan Corporation since July 2009. He served as a Director of Atlas Energy GP, LLC, the General Partner of Atlas Energy, L.P from February 2011 to February 2015. Mr. Biderman served as a Director of Atlas Energy Group, LLC since February 2015. He served as a Director of Atlas Energy, Inc. from July 2009 to February 2011. Mr. Biderman served as a Director of Home Loan Servicing Solutions, Ltd. He serves as a Member of Advisory Council at Circle Peak Capital, L.L.C. Mr. Biderman served as a Director of National Financial Partners Corp. (now NFP Corp.). He has been an Independent Director at Apollo Residential Mortgage, Inc., since July 2011. Mr. Biderman is a Treasurer and serves on the Board of Governors of Hebrew Union College-Jewish Institute of Religion and serves on the Advisory Council of the Program in Judaic Studies of Princeton University. He was First Team Bank Analyst from 1974 to 1976. Mr. Biderman has more than 40 years of business and financial experience. He is a Chartered Financial Analyst. Mr. Biderman received his B.S.E. from Princeton University in 1967 and his M.B.A. from Harvard University in 1969.Read Full Background




